}}</ref>

==Genetic history==
Based on molecular data, a [[population bottleneck]] among ancestors of modern Finns is estimated to have occurred about 4000 years ago.<ref name="pmid8876258">{{cite journal
| author = Sajantila A, Salem AH, Savolainen P, Bauer K, Gierig C, Pääbo S
| title = Paternal and maternal DNA lineages reveal a bottleneck in the founding of the Finnish population
| journal = Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America
| volume = 93
| issue = 21
| pages = 12035–9
| year = 1996
| month = October
| pmid = 8876258
| pmc = 38178
| doi = 10.1073/pnas.93.21.12035
| url = 
| issn = 
}}</ref>  This bottleneck resulted in exceptionally low diversity in the [[Y chromosome]], estimated to reflect the survival of just two ancestral male lineages.<ref name="pmid10229384">{{cite journal
| author = Kittles RA, Bergen AW, Urbanek M, Virkkunen M, Linnoila M, Goldman D, Long JC
| title = Autosomal, mitochondrial, and Y chromosome DNA variation in Finland: evidence for a male-specific bottleneck
| journal = American Journal of Physical Anthropology
| volume = 108
| issue = 4
| pages = 381–99
| year = 1999
| month = April
| pmid = 10229384
| doi = 10.1002/(SICI)1096-8644(199904)108:4<381::AID-AJPA1>3.0.CO;2-5
| url = 
| issn = 
}}</ref><ref name="pmid10352935">{{cite journal
| author = Lahermo P, Savontaus ML, Sistonen P, Béres J, de Knijff P, Aula P, Sajantila A
| title = Y chromosomal polymorphisms reveal founding lineages in the Finns and the Saami
| journal = European Journal of Human Genetics
| volume = 7
| issue = 4
| pages = 447–58
| year = 1999
| pmid = 10352935
| doi = 10.1038/sj.ejhg.5200316
| url = 
| issn = 
}}</ref>  The distribution of Y chromosome [[haplotype]]s within Finland is consistent with two separate founding settlements, in eastern and western Finland.<ref name="pmid9545401">{{cite journal
| author = Kittles RA, Perola M, Peltonen L, Bergen AW, Aragon RA, Virkkunen M, Linnoila M, Goldman D, Long JC
| title = Dual origins of Finns revealed by Y chromosome haplotype variation
| journal = American Journal of Human Genetics
| volume = 62
| issue = 5
| pages = 1171–9
| year = 1998
| month = May
| pmid = 9545401
| pmc = 1377088
| doi = 10.1086/301831
| url = 
| issn = 
}}</ref>  The population bottleneck is seen only in the Y chromosome.  Genetic diversity in [[autosomal]] chromosomes and in [[mitochondrial DNA]] (maternally inherited) is as high among Finns as among other European ethnic groups.<ref name="pmid9545401"/>

The Finnish disease heritage has been attributed to this 4000-year-old bottleneck.<ref name="pmid8876258"/>  The geographic distribution and family pedigrees associated with some Finnish heritage disease mutations has linked the enrichment in these mutations to multiple local [[founder effect]]s, some associated with a period of "late settlement" in the 16th century (see [[History of Finland]]).<ref name="pmid10469845">{{cite journal
| author = Peltonen L, Jalanko A, Varilo T
| title = Molecular genetics of the Finnish disease heritage
| journal = Human Molecular Genetics
| volume = 8
| issue = 10
| pages = 1913–23
| year = 1999
| pmid = 10469845
| doi = 10.1093/hmg/8.10.1913
| url = 
| issn = 
}}</ref>

